        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(E\\)</span> un espace euclidien et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(u\\in O (E)\\)</span> telle que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\ker (u-id) \\neq E\\)</span>. Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x\\in E\\)</span> tel que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(u (x) \\neq x\\)</span>. On pose <span class=\"math inline\">\\(y = u (x)\\)</span>. Alors on sait qu’il existe une unique réflexion <span class=\"math inline\">\\(r\\)</span> telle que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(r (y) = x\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
